{
  "stem": "26111.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we realized what a hell it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because while you're in it, you sort of always try to look on the bright side.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, but I can still go to the theater.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes, but I can still go to that restaurant, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe there is one that does still admit Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe there, there was--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After Kristallnacht, you couldn't rationalize those things anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was just pure hell, just pure hell, from that point of view, not loss of life yet, but pure hell.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Relief, relief.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was presented immediately as a temporary separation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the idea that-- and my father was-- did this very well.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, he was a-- he was a psychoanalyst, [LAUGHS] and he knew me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he knew that I was very much, probably in the sense of pride, in the sense of pride of person, I was suffering very deeply from, from this club that was always poised over me.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And and it was-- even though my way out, the way-- the only way that I could, until then, think of was, was, was Palestine, Zionism, even though that was so opposed to what he had believed in all these many years, he still recognized my thinking and respected it for what it was.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I think he had a very-- but he knew also that, of course, the separation was the one fly in the ointment, and-- from them, from the family.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so he, he somehow knew to present it in such a way that the separation would be temporary, the reuniting would be-- would happen.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That came first.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the, the, the, the, the getting out of hell came second.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
